# Workflow: Push to Clay

When the operator says "push to clay", "send to clay", or wants to push leads to a Clay table, follow this flow.

## Prerequisites
The operator must have pulled leads first (via "pull leads" workflow). If not, redirect them.

## Step 1: Get Webhook URL
Ask: "Paste the Clay webhook URL"
Validate: Must start with `https://api.clay.com/` and contain `webhook`.

## Step 2: Confirm Blank Table
Ask: "Is this a BLANK Clay table (not a template)? Clay auto-creates columns from our JSON keys on blank tables. Templates require manual column mapping."

## Step 3: Preview
Show what will be sent for 1 sample lead:
- Identity: email, first_name, last_name, full_name, job_title
- Company: company_name, company_domain, company_website, industry, employee_count
- Enrichment: monthly_visits, lcp, tti, aov
- Verification: email_verified, email_verified_at, is_catchall, mx_provider
- Segment: segment_id, segment_name
- Recipe: recipe_id, recipe_version
- Existing outputs (if any)

Show total count: "Will push {N} leads"

## Step 4: Test Push (1 Lead)
"Push 1 test lead first?" (recommended)
POST single JSON object to webhook URL. Show response.
Ask operator to verify in Clay.

## Step 5: Push All
Push remaining leads ONE AT A TIME. Show progress every 25.
Use 0.1s delay between requests.

## Critical Rules
- ALWAYS send ONE lead per POST (single JSON object, NOT an array)
- Clay webhook does NOT accept arrays
- If all pushes fail, the webhook URL is likely wrong
- Log any failures with the lead email for debugging
